    "body": "Closes #11781 \r\n\r\nUse `spack-build-<type>.txt` for `log` and `env` filenames, where `<type>` is `out` and `env` respectively.  \r\n\r\nAddendum:  Install `log` and `env` filenames should have the same form.\r\n\r\nTODO:\r\n- [x] Test modified packages\r\n- [x] Rename `check_install` to `check_mpileaks_install` in cmd/env.py tests\r\n- [x] Remove relative path option from install log and env path methods\r\n- [x] Support build filename backward compatibility (did build and install)\r\n- [x] Ensure metadata (sub)directory exists prior to installing build log and env files \r\n- [x] Rename `check_removal` to `check_viewdir_removal` in cmd/env.py tests\r\n- [x] Clarify package build/install path property docstrings\r\n- [x] Remove unused `mock_log` from `install.py` tests\r\n- [x] Remove unused `spec` is `None` from `directory_layout`s `metadata_path` and `build_packages_path`",
    "performed_via_github_app": null
